Class FIRFilter

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<SampleChunk>

    public abstract class FIRFilter
extends FixedSizeSampleAudioProcessor
    FIR filter is a multiplication of the frequency domain of a signal with the frequency domain of a filter. That corresponds to a convolution in the time domain; that is, a weighted sum of the previous input.
    Author:
    David Dupplaw (dpd@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
